                            <comment id="14467000" author="werdna" created="Thu, 14 May 2009 22:35:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ps- only tried this on 1.6.1, but might be a bug in other versions, too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467017" author="blackdrag" created="Fri, 15 May 2009 17:34:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;changed &quot;Verify error&quot; to &quot;java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: groovy/lang/GroovyObject&quot;, since this is no VerifyError&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466863" author="werdna" created="Fri, 15 May 2009 17:41:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes.  It is NoClassDefFoundError when running on the command line and VerifyError when running in Eclipse.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466919" author="blackdrag" created="Sat, 16 May 2009 07:11:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I hope you are not angry at me for changing the title once again. The problem you see with the command line is not reproducible here. Usually that is a setup problem, not related to the VerifyError. The VerifyError again should not happen. The message is like this: java.lang.VerifyError: (class: pack/FromSrc, method: main signature: ([Ljava/lang/String;)Ljava/lang/Object&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; Incompatible type for getting or setting field&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As usual the message does not tell very much. But looking at the source I can see a static method trying to access a non static property. This should lead at last to a MissingPropertyExeption, better fail at compile time. A VerifyError is not acceptable. Because of that I raised the level to critical&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466954" author="werdna" created="Sat, 16 May 2009 14:53:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;True...should have realized that...a static method accessing non-static field.  Not angry at all.  Thanks for looking at this.  &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466971" author="blackdrag" created="Mon, 18 May 2009 08:07:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467032" author="roshandawrani" created="Tue, 19 May 2009 01:30:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shouldn&apos;t this issue be assigned - for process&apos; sake?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466935" author="werdna" created="Tue, 19 May 2009 04:55:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Done. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467018" author="blackdrag" created="Tue, 19 May 2009 05:03:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;thanks, I forgot to do that part myself &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
